The paper proposes a semi-supervised clustering model that combines expert knowledge with the true distribution of data. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), data mining (cs.DM), or social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on finding clusters in partially categorized data sets, machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM) are the most likely sub-categories.
